eneration/order helpers are insufficient to catch real startup sequencing defects. No subprocess requirement.","test_description":"Use a fresh local Postgres schema with no `_migrations` table and one migration that depends on `_migrations` existence indirectly via runner bookkeeping. Run runner once. Assert `_migrations` exists and contains the applied version, and run completes without missing-table errors.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
